This paper deals with domain adaptation, which is a common problem in machine learning. The paper proposes a new algorithm for multi-source domain adaptation, which involves adjusting the weight of each source domain during training. This algorithm is evaluated on real-world sentiment analysis and digit recognition datasets. Given this, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves some theoretical analysis, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves some natural language processing, which suggests that cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is another possible sub-category.
